## Agent Working Conventions

- Always respond in Simplified Chinese for this project.
- Before implementing code, check the relevant design docs above and preserve the current architecture decisions.
- Prefer updating shared domain types and API contracts before implementing app-specific code.
- Do not duplicate API request / response types across frontend, backend, and CLI.
- Keep backend workflow logic centralized in the backend workflow module.
- Keep Skills free of tokens and raw HTTP details; Skills should call `proud-flow` CLI helper commands.
- Do not reintroduce a separate first-version tool server unless the design docs are explicitly changed.

